JSSCLI(1)					      User Commands					       JSSCLI(1)

NAME
       jsscli - JSON-first CLI for the JSS / Frappe REST API

SYNOPSIS
       jsscli [-q|-v...]  [--profile name] COMMAND [options...]

DESCRIPTION
       jsscli is a fast, secure, and scriptable command-line client for any Frappe/ERPNext or Juragan Subsystem site. It
       provides	 full access to REST resources, custom server methods, file operations, and document attachments, with a
       consistent JSON output and built-in session management.

       All output is JSON. When stdout is a terminal, the JSON is colourised and indented;  when  piped	 or  redirected,
       plain  pretty-printed  JSON  is	used.	Errors are also printed as JSON to stderr, making integration with shell
       pipelines and automation tools straightforward.

       Sensitive credentials (passwords, API secrets) are stored in the system keyring; session	 data  is  encrypted  at
       rest using AES‑256‑GCM with a key derived via HKDF and a random salt.

GLOBAL OPTIONS
       -q, --quiet
	      Suppress non-error messages printed to stderr (e.g., progress hints).

       -v, --verbose
	      Increase log verbosity (can be repeated). Affects internal logging only; does not change JSON output.

       --profile name
	      Use  the	specified  account  profile instead of the active account. Overrides the JSS_PROFILE environment
	      variable.

COMMANDS
   auth
       Manage authentication for the active account.

       jsscli auth login
	      Authenticate using stored credentials. On success, a session is saved locally  and  reused  by  subsequent
	      commands. Output example:
	      {"ok":true, "account":"prod", "full_name":"John Doe", "sitename":"mysite", "roles":["System Manager"]}

       jsscli auth logout
	      End the server session and remove the local session record.

       jsscli auth status
	      Show whether a valid session exists for the active account.

       jsscli auth whoami
	      Display the full name, sitename, and roles of the authenticated user.

   account
       Manage named account profiles. Account definitions are stored in ~/.config/jsscli/accounts.toml; secrets are kept
       in the system keyring.

       jsscli account add name [options]
	      Create a new account.

	      --url URL
		     (Required) Base URL of the Frappe site (e.g., https://mysite.example.com).

	      --mode session|token
		     Authentication mode (default: session).

	      --email email
		     Required for session mode.

	      --password pass
		     Password; if omitted you will be prompted securely.

	      --api-key key
		     Required for token mode.

	      --api-secret sec
		     Required for token mode.

	      --sitename name
		     Expected site name (optional; used for validation).

	      --activate
		     Set this account as active immediately.

       jsscli account list
	      List all accounts; active one is marked with active:true.

       jsscli account use name
	      Switch the active account to name.

       jsscli account remove name
	      Delete an account and all associated secrets.

       jsscli account show [name]
	      Show detailed information for an account (secrets are masked).

   config
       jsscli config set key value
	      Set a configuration key. Special key active_account sets the active account (same as account use).

       jsscli config get key
	      Print the value of a configuration key.

       jsscli config list
	      List all current settings.

       jsscli config init
	      Create the configuration directory and default files.

       jsscli config path
	      Print the absolute path to the configuration file.

   doctype
       Perform CRUD operations on any DocType.

       jsscli doctype get doctype name
	      Retrieve a single document. Output contains a top-level "data" key.

       jsscli doctype list doctype [options]
	      List documents matching filters.

	      --fields f1,f2,...
		     Comma-separated list of fields to return.

	      --filter field,op,value
		     Filter condition (e.g., status,=,Active). Can be repeated.

	      --limit n
		     Maximum number of records (default: 20).

	      --start n
		     Offset for pagination.

	      --order-by field
		     Sort field (append	 desc for descending order).

       jsscli doctype create doctype [file]
	      Create a new document. Data is read from a JSON file (or stdin if file is -).

       jsscli doctype update doctype name [file]
	      Update an existing document using JSON from file (or stdin).

       jsscli doctype delete doctype name [-y|--yes]
	      Delete a document. Confirmation is required unless -y is supplied.

   file
       Manage files and attachments.

       jsscli file upload file doctype docname fieldname
	      Upload a local file (max 50 MB) and attach it to the specified document.

       jsscli file download url [-o path] [-y|--yes]
	      Download a file from a relative URL (e.g., /files/report.pdf). If no -o is given, the file is saved in the
	      current directory with the basename from the URL.

       jsscli file list [options]
	      List files from a folder (default: Home) with flexible filters.

	      --folder path
		     Folder to list (default: "Home").

	      --limit n
		     Maximum number of files (default: 50).

	      --search pattern
		     Filter by file name (substring match).

	      --file-type pattern
		     Filter by file MIME type (substring match).

	      --attached-to-doctype doctype
		     Filter by linked document type.

	      --attached-to-name docname
		     Filter by linked document name.

   attachments
       jsscli attachments doctype name
	      Scan a document for file attachments (fields with values like /private/files/... or /files/...). A list of
	      files  is displayed and you are prompted to download all, cancel, or select specific files by index (e.g.,
	      1,3).

   files
       jsscli files number
	      Convenience command that accepts a single identifier:

	      •	     If number starts with "ODR-", it is treated as a Data Pengajuan document name.

	      •	     Otherwise, it is treated as a no_perjanjian (loan agreement number); the corresponding Master  Data
		     Nasabah  record  is fetched to obtain its register_id, and then attachments from the Data Pengajuan
		     doctype with that ID are listed.

	      The attachment download prompt is then shown, identical to attachments.

   call-method
       jsscli call-method method.path [--args key=val,key=val...]
	      Call any server-side Python method. Arguments are passed as a JSON object.  This command is the Swiss army
	      knife for executing custom logic, lazy-loaded child tables, workspace queries, and reports.

	      Examples:
	      jsscli call-method "juragan.ops...get_lazy_child_rows" --args docname=OD-...,tab=informasi_bpkb_tab
	      jsscli call-method "frappe.desk.query_report.run" --args report_name=Stok_TTS,filters={}

   search
       jsscli search query [options]
	      Perform a global search across all DocTypes.

	      --limit n
		     Maximum number of results (default: 20).

	      --doctype doctype
		     Restrict search to a specific DocType.

   tunggakan
       jsscli tunggakan no_rekening_kredit
	      Retrieve the detailed outstanding debt breakdown for a given credit account number. This calls the  server
	      method  juragan.ops.doctype.master_data_nasabah.master_data_nasabah.cek_rincian_hutang_nasabah and returns
	      its JSON response. Useful for obtaining the raw data before generating the printable "Kartu Piutang".

   kp
       jsscli kp no_perjanjian
	      Generate and download the "Form Rincian Sisa Piutang Nasabah" PDF	 (receivable  card)  for  a  given  loan
	      agreement number.

	      The command performs the following steps:

	      1.     Find the customer record in Master Data Nasabah using no_perjanjian.

	      2.     Extract no_rekening_kredit (credit account number) and the document name.

	      3.     Call  the server method cek_rincian_hutang_nasabah with the account number to ensure the receivable
		     data is computed on the server.

	      4.     Download the PDF using the print format "Form Rincian Sisa Piutang Nasabah" (without letterhead).

	      5.     Save the PDF in the system's Downloads folder with	 a  filename  like  Rincian_Sisa_Piutang_<agree‐
		     ment>.pdf.

	      If  the  server  method fails or the receivable data is still not available, the PDF will contain a place‐
	      holder message. Ensure the customer has outstanding data before running this command.

   info
       jsscli info
	      Print detailed build and version information, including Git hash, branch, commit count,  build  timestamp,
	      compiler	versions,  and target platform.	 This data is embedded at compile time and does not require net‐
	      work access.

   changelog
       jsscli changelog [-n count]
	      Display the Git commit history embedded at build time (up to 50 commits).	 If the binary was built outside
	      a Git repository, an empty list is returned.

   manual
       jsscli manual
	      Open the built-in manual in a terminal pager (scrollable, searchable).  Press q to quit.

ENVIRONMENT
       JSS_PROFILE
	      Name of the account profile to use (overridden by --profile).

       JSS_EMAIL
	      Default email when adding a session-based account.

       JSS_ACTIVE_ACCOUNT
	      Overrides the active_account setting in config.toml.

       Standard proxy variables (HTTPS_PROXY, HTTP_PROXY, NO_PROXY) are respected by the underlying HTTP client.

FILES
       ~/.config/jsscli/config.toml
	      Global settings (active account, defaults).

       ~/.config/jsscli/accounts.toml
	      Account definitions (no secrets).

       ~/.cache/jsscli/session.enc
	      Encrypted session data.

       ~/.cache/jsscli/.session.salt
	      Salt file for encryption key derivation.

EXIT STATUS
       0      Success.

       1      Generic runtime error (e.g., I/O, parse error).

       2      Invalid usage or input.

       3      Not authenticated (no valid session).

       4      Network error (connection, timeout).

       5      API error (non-2xx HTTP response from server).

EXAMPLES
       Add an account and log in:

	      jsscli account add prod --url https://frappe.example.com --email admin@example.com --activate
	      jsscli auth login

       List active customers:
	      jsscli doctype list "Master Data Nasabah" --filter status,=,Aktif --fields name,nama_nasabah,no_perjanjian
	      --limit 10

       Download all attachments from a loan agreement:
	      jsscli files 6001-0000053-0001
	      (then select y to download all files)

       Search for documents containing "VIXION":
	      jsscli search VIXION --doctype "Master Data Nasabah" --limit 5

       Check outstanding debt details:
	      jsscli tunggakan 6001-0000053-0001

       Generate the receivable card PDF:
	      jsscli kp 6001-0000053-0001

       Call a custom server method:
	      jsscli	     call-method	 "juragan.collection.utils.get_combined_collection_data"	  --args
	      date_from=2026-07-01,date_to=2026-07-31

       Show build information:
	      jsscli info

SEE ALSO
       librjss(3), frappe(7)
       Frappe REST API documentation: https://frappeframework.com/docs

